@chapter Custom Prompt Builder

@float Figure,fig:screenshot_cpb
@center @image{screenshots/bashstyle-ng_cpb,,, BashStyle-NG Custom Prompt Builder, png}
@caption{Custom Prompt Builder}
@end float

@float Figure,fig:screenshot_cpb-toolbox
@center @image{screenshots/bashstyle-ng_cpb-toolbox,,, BashStyle-NG CPB Toolbox, png}
@caption{CPB - Toolbox}
@end float

@b{BashStyle-NG} contains a Custom Prompt Builder that allows you to create a
prompt from scratch, or modify one the existing prompt styles shipped with
@b{BasShtyle-NG}.

You can insert symbolic colors into your prompt, which will allow you to change
the colors right from the Styles Settings.

The Toolbox allows you to insert informations into your prompt, both Bash default
and @b{BashStyle-NG} specific functions.

@defvr {Setting} use_custom_prompt Use Custom Prompt
This master setting makes @b{BashStyle-NG} use your prompt definied here.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} command PROMPT_COMMAND
Everything here goes into your PROMPT_COMMAND.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} prompt PS1
Everything here goes into your PS1.
@end defvr
